    "answer_id" : 79656761,
    "question_id" : 76772549,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I got the same error and didn't understand why.</p>\n<p>Read the documentation <a href=\"https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/reference/integration/rest-clients.html#rest-request-factories\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">rest-request-factories</a>\nI realized that when the HttpComponentsClientHttpRequestFactory is used, the httpclient5 library is needed.\nAdded to pom.xml for maven, dependency</p>\n<pre><code>&lt;dependency&gt;\n    &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.httpcomponents.client5&lt;/groupId&gt;\n    &lt;artifactId&gt;httpclient5&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n    &lt;version&gt;5.5&lt;/version&gt;\n&lt;/dependency&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Everything is working! :)</p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 187094,
        "reputation" : 5301,
        "user_id" : 424903,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/8oHZF.png?s=256",
        "display_name" : "Gimby",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/424903/gimby"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 1,
      "creation_date" : 1763034087,
      "post_id" : 79818486,
      "comment_id" : 140852254,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "When you&#39;ve got one problem, you&#39;ve got multiple problems. Run a <code>mvn dependency:tree -Dverbose=true</code> and find out. Using the verbose flag, Maven will tell you exactly which dependencies it excluded because it conflicted with another existing dependency. That way you can see which different versions of the same dependency are trying to enter into your classpath and where they come from, and which Maven is silently removing."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 18162111,
      "reputation" : 23,
      "user_id" : 13213344,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgvC6sSzNuGcv-Q4vjz2vQFnC87dfThxPh5P5pR=k-s256",
      "display_name" : "Madhura Maddipatla",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/13213344/madhura-maddipatla"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1763016044,
    "last_edit_date" : 1763016044,
    "creation_date" : 1763014030,
    "answer_id" : 79818486,
    "question_id" : 76772549,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In my case I had both dependencies. To resolve the issue, I needed to remove <strong>httpCore5</strong>. Let <strong>httpClient5</strong> provide <strong>httpCore</strong>:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;dependency&gt;\n  &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.httpcomponents.core5&lt;/groupId&gt;\n  &lt;artifactId&gt;httpcore5&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n  &lt;version&gt;5.3.6&lt;/version&gt;\n&lt;/dependency&gt;\n\n&lt;dependency&gt;\n  &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.httpcomponents.client5&lt;/groupId&gt;\n  &lt;artifactId&gt;httpclient5&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n  &lt;version&gt;5.5&lt;/version&gt;\n&lt;/dependency&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
